<br>
After listening to many proposals on  FCFS, FFA, or Reservations I have a proposal to put before the Brell Community. I believe this proposal if adopted could settle the differences between the majority of people playing on Brell server. I do say majority because it is impossible to make 100% perfectly happy.<br>
<br>
To start out with this system Brell would have to wipe clean all raid reservations as of March 1st. This would be 1st day of a new system.<br>
<br>
Feb 1st to Feb 7th every guild on Brell that would wish to participate would be allowed to vote on 20 guilds that would administrate raid reservations. Each guild would get to submit a list of 20 guilds that they feel would best represent the server as a board. The 20 guilds that receive the most votes would then make up this board. From this group of 20 guilds a representative will be appointed from each and a co-representative in case that person is away. These 20 also will choose 1 additional guild not from the 20. This 1 guild chosen by the 20 will become the 21st and chairperson of this raid board.<br>
<br>
The duties of these 21 will be to vote and determine 34 guilds and 4 independents that have proven records of raid organization and the ability to lead them. It will be this boards determination by vote to choose 38 raid leaders.<br>
<br>
Once these 38 guilds and Indy’s are chosen they will be randomly rolled and listed in order of roll. 1-38. All guilds and chosen Indies will then submit 2 raid reservation intentions to the panel. Only 1 weekend raid intention per guild or Indy to be allowed. The random number rolled will determine preference when raids are submitted. I would say Feb 8th to 13Th 5 days to submit. Anyone not submitting with in 5 days would not be able to reserve dates.  Adjustment period of 5 days Feb 14th to 19Th. Final raid calendar for the month of March to be posted following adjustments for dual raids submitted.<br>
<br>
This in total would allow 76 raids to have firm reservations. Be it VS, Fear, Sky, Hate, Trak, FGs, Naggy, Vox Epics whatever the raid intentions are. These raids would have a firm commitment of reservation and be honored by the majority of Brell. Dragon mobs would still be listed on rotation for the month only. So if you choose one of these and don’t get your shot then you would lose the raid do to new calendar the following month.The 38 guilds that have received random numbers would have them reversed the following month so last would be 1st etc. New numbers rolled every other month.<br>
<br>
The effect of this system would open up areas to FCFS on more non-booked nights. It would allow guilds and Indy’s to plan raids 1 month in advance getting support they need.<br>
It would dispose of long lists on boss mobs and dragons. No more camping boards. And best of all open up adventuring and raids to those that want to do things on a whim. This would be a very fair system to everyone. Every guild would be given a vote of which they thought would be the most fair to represent Brell on the board. This board in essence would be Brells representative’s chosen by the majority and representing the majority views.<br>
<br>
